-- Euro Extends Gain Versus Dollar as Draghi Says Euro Irreversible
-- B y   L u c y   M e a k i n
-- 2012-10-04T12:37:34Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-10-04/euro-extends-gain-versus-dollar-as-draghi-says-euro-irreversible.html
The euro extended an advance against
the dollar after European Central Bank President  Mario Draghi 
said the common currency is “irreversible.”  The 17-member currency strengthened 0.6 percent to $1.2981
at 1:37 p.m. London time. It rose 0.7 percent to 102.05 yen.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Lucy Meakin in London at 
